 \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Surface aldehydes with supercritical methanethiol route\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface photochemical/discharge aldehydes converge with hydrothermal supercritical-CO2 methanethiol production before the core Strecker sequence.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_001\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Miller-1958 style sulfur-rich discharge route\",\n      \"description\": \"A sulfur-rich CH4/CO2/H2S/NH3 discharge environment generates the key feedstocks documented in archival Miller samples, followed by the established acrolein-methional-Strecker corridor.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Mixed hydrothermal-surface systems chemistry route\",\n      \"description\": \"A maximum-interconnection path in which hydrothermal aldehydes and methanethiol are supplemented by surface HCN generation before surface acrolein, methional, aminonitrile, and final hydrolysis.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_011\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_001\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_012\", \"mol_006\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_009\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_004\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_011\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_012\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_006\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Methionine", "overall_strategy": "This network is centered on the only experimentally verified prebiotic corridor to methionine identified in the literature: aldehyde generation, acrolein formation by aldol condensation of formaldehyde and acetaldehyde, Michael addition of methanethiol to acrolein to give methional, Strecker conversion of methional to the corresponding aminonitrile, and hydrolysis to methionine. Ten distinct pathways are provided as distinct precursor-sourcing and environment-coupling routes that all converge on the same literature-supported core target-forming sequence rather than inventing unsupported alternative terminal chemistries. Hydrothermal chemistry primarily supplies methanethiol under FeS- or MoS2-mediated conditions and can also contribute aldehyde precursors; surface spark-discharge/photochemical and evaporitic chemistry supplies HCN, NH3, formaldehyde, acetaldehyde, and acrolein; biochemical/prebiotic stages complete hydrolysis and network integration. The network explicitly addresses the key bottleneck from the literature: methanethiol availability.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", 